This is a known issue. Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30+), and .NET 10 MAUI defaults to edge-to-edge rendering, which breaks the old approach. Here's what to do:

## Recommended Fix: Listen to keyboard insets (Android)

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`, use the modern `WindowInsets` API:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for keyboard (IME) inset changes
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navBar   = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Pad the bottom of the content by the keyboard height
            // (minus nav bar so it doesn't double-pad when keyboard is hidden)
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom - navBar.Bottom, 0);
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

## iOS

iOS generally handles this automatically. If not, set `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default in .NET 10):

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs — usually no change needed, but to be explicit:
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(h => { })
       .ConfigureKeyboardAutoManagerScroll();  // default: enabled
```

## Chat layout tip

Structure your XAML so the input bar is **outside** the `CollectionView`:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}"
                    ItemsUpdatingScrollMode="KeepLastItemInView" />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

The insets listener above will pad the `DecorView`, pushing the entire layout (including your bottom `Entry`) above the keyboard. No `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust` needed.
